53% of patients who come to the Victor-Gadbois home come from their homes, 47% from hospitals.
Problems with access to palliative care
It is said that 77% of Canadians simply do not have access to palliative care, ie care that is designed to alleviate suffering once a patient reaches the final stage of their life, whether at home, in a hospital or in a nursing home. .
