Believers will walk here the Way of Pain or the Way of the Cross (Latin Via Dolorosa).
It begins at the fortress of Antonia - Pretoria - where the trial took place, walks through the streets of the Old Town and leads to the Temple of the Holy Sepulcher on Mount Golgotha - the place of crucifixion, the anointing stone and the place where Jesus was buried.
Here is the symbolic Christian navel of the world, which symbolizes the salvation of humanity.
And the Holy Cross Monastery in Jerusalem was built on the site where, according to Christian legend, a tree grew, from which they made a cross for the crucifixion of Jesus.
Jerusalem also houses the holiest site for Jews - the Wailing Wall, the rest of the temple, which was destroyed by the Romans in 70 AD.
According to tradition, people of different faiths leave notes with wishes here, which are then filled in.
Take the path vertically
The ruins of the fortress of Masada remained from a secret hiding place from the enemy, which Herod the Great built in 25 BC for his family.
The ruins are located on cliffs in the mountains at an altitude of 450 m above sea level.
Only those who are involved in mountaineering can get to it on their own.
The cable car will take the others to this historic mountain.
