Traveling by all types of public transport costs 6 shekels, for which you can drive with a change of 1.5 hours.
According to Jewish tradition, Shabbat is celebrated on Saturday in Israel.
From Friday evening until sunset on Saturday, work stops in markets, shops and public transport.
And the work week starts on Sunday morning.
In many cafes, restaurants and hotels, you only get kosher food: with the exception of pork, seafood, unscaled fish and dishes that contain a combination of milk and meat.
They offer a large selection of lamb and beef dishes, soups and desserts, prepared from coconut milk, traditional Jewish porridge hummus, various types of sauces, balls of ground chickpeas - falafel, fruits and vegetables.
