Simon Ornest: We want to gather positive energy at concerts
What do you think about the end of the world in less than a month?
It&#39;s just one of the other alarms we humans like to catch.
Together with The Tap Tap, we make fun of it and say that we are the only band in the world that can gather enough positive energy to delay or prevent the end of the world.
In addition, in December you will organize a completely unique project of three concerts against the end of the world.
Can you introduce it to readers?
This is a nationwide charity event, which we have been planning for two years.
We have decided to use the marketing potential of the end of the Mayan calendar announced on December 21 at 11:10 am.
The day before December 20 from 9 pm, 3 concerts will take place simultaneously in Prague, Brno and Ostrava.
They will end around the time the Mayan calendar ends on the Pacific island of Kiribati, which is 12 hours ahead of us.
Who came up with this idea?
Originally it was probably my idea, then we came up with everything together with our artist Honza Augusta.
In addition to accumulating enough positive energy and preventing the end of the world, we also want to think with the public about the state in which we will one day pass this world on to our children.
On the occasion of the end of the Mayan calendar, we also created a unique collection of shoes, T-shirts, bags or original keys against the end of the world, which people can also support us by purchasing at www.e-tap.cz.
The Tap Tap, along with other performers, also sang the so-called anthem against the end of the world, called &quot;End of the World Canceled&quot;.
It is already very popular on YouTube, will it also be performed at these benefit concerts?
Of course, at the very end, that is, if we succeed and the end of the world does not come ...
It is sung by all the performers at all three concerts simultaneously.
The anthems are suddenly connected in a unique live broadcast on Czech Television.
He wrote the lyrics to this song and the main role of Jesus in the clip is played by Tomáš Hanák, Xindl X also sings in it ...
How did you get to work with them?
We also cooperate with other personalities of the Czech cultural scene, given that we organize a lot of charity events and concerts ...
We try to involve them intensively in these projects.
It turned out that most of them are interested in and enjoy working with us.
What will the proceeds from concerts against the end of the world go to?
To equip the barrier-free educational center Studeo, which we have been implementing for the sixth year with the civic association Tap at the Jedlička Institute.
Students of the Jedliček Institute regularly attend lecturers and engage in activities that entertain and interest them.
The students themselves do not have the means to go to the lecturers themselves, so we try to make it possible for them in this way.
As part of the completion of the Jedlička Institute, a separate building will be built in the future, to which we will move with this project.
Several bands and performers will perform at each concert.
How did you choose them?
We tried to put together a program that will appeal to all generations, including children.
For example, Chinaski, Support Lesbiens, Illustratosphere with Dan Bárta, The Tap Tap, Marián Bango and Jiří Suchý will perform in Prague.
You can find all the details at www.kpks.cz.
Are you planning any similar &quot;bombastic events&quot; in the future?
In May, we will perform at the Prague Spring for the first time, so we will definitely prepare an interesting program with interesting guests here as well.
Next year we would also like to play at the Czech National House in New York, and I personally, when we are already in the USA, I would like to connect it with performances in Washington and Chicago.
Your foreign plans are not minimalist, so far you have performed in Madrid, Brussels, London or Moscow.
However, The Tap Tap is a group of handicapped people.
How do you manage these journeys logistically and organizationally?
It&#39;s not as bad as it seems at first glance.
We have five members in an electric wheelchair, their wheelchairs have to travel in the trunk, and of course we carry a large amount of cargo and tool boxes with us ...
However, so far it has always been possible without any problems, CSA and British Airways were very prepared for us, that I wondered how many times.
Even in Moscow, from which we returned recently, it was without problems.
Thanks to trips abroad, you can compare how individuals differ in accessibility, public access to the disabled and the like.
What have you encountered so far?
After Madrid, Luxembourg, London and other places where everything works better than here, we have witnessed in Russia that everything in the East is still in its infancy.
Compared to Prague, Moscow is very barrier-free, here it is still unusual for a person in an electric wheelchair to move alone in the city center.
There are no such obvious things there, such as that you prefer wheelchair users in the elevator.
Fortunately, civic associations are already being set up there, which try to draw attention to the problems of people with disabilities.
And what, on the contrary, do we still have to catch up with more developed countries?
There are a lot of things we are still behind ...
But it is important to mention that improving and refining the situation always depends on the efforts of the people concerned.
It is quite common in London and Madrid that even people with severe disabilities move independently in public, they can go to the toilet, to the museum, anywhere ...
However, it is not very common for a large number of people with disabilities to take an active part in social life, on the contrary, we are a little ahead of that with The Tap Tap!
Respecting the public or accessibility is one thing, but only when we become important athletes, artists, actors, politicians or lawyers will things really start to change.
So far, these are isolated cases of people who have a strong will.
The band The Tap Tap is very popular at the moment, but let&#39;s go back a few years, what made you start it in 1998?
I joined the Jedlička Institute as an educator, where I had many young people around me who were interested in doing something.
And since I&#39;m a musician myself, I play the saxophone, among other things, so I founded a hobby music group with a colleague.
And over time, as our moderator Láďa Angelovič says, it got a little out of hand (laughs).
But popularity came in recent years, or am I wrong?
It&#39;s true that it helped us when we started connecting with well-known singers and also actively working on the promotion of the band.
We realized that work that is not visible basically does not exist.
Thanks to contributions from the European Union, we can also afford quality lecturers, equipment and so on.
Was your goal to make it so high with The Tap Tap?
From the beginning, I felt the potential for something to be done differently.
Showbusiness is full of things where one mimics the other.
It is logical in a way, everything new is received carefully and it takes a long time.
There are very few things that are unique, but I dare say that Tap Tap are one of them.
The first impression of a person who sees us for the first time is, of course, regret, it is natural ...
But that regret is completely useless, because people with disabilities are no sufferers of all abandoned beings that we must regret.
These are people who can live a full life and develop, provided, of course, that they have the resources to do so.
I say that when people with disabilities succeed, it is not just a shift for them, but for society as a whole.
Did the fact that you are a strict boss, as many people called you, also helped this success?
If we want to do quality work, we must be uncompromising in many things and require a certain discipline.
But I think that&#39;s perfectly normal.
Some people come to us with a romantic idea and with their heads in the clouds, and when they find out that they have to go to rehearsal twice a week, go to a preparation and spend a lot of time traveling to concerts, their enthusiasm quickly leaves them.
But this is how it works everywhere, in every group that wants to work and that wants to achieve something.
The Tap Tap currently has twenty members.
How many of them were at its beginnings in 1998?
Only one Lada Angelovic.
We are an open group, people leave and come, this cannot be prevented.
Whoever has the will and taste always has the door open with us
