As research shows, sometimes not, because in its extreme form it can lead people to take absurd physical risks, gamble or abuse addictive substances as a way to alleviate it.
On the other hand, many philosophers and writers have discussed the connection between boredom and creativity, said Professor Vodanovich, who has studied the problem for more than two decades.
&quot;Boredom is the way the brain tells you that you should do something else,&quot; said Gary Marcus, a professor of psychology at NYU.
But the brain doesn&#39;t always know the best thing to do.
If you get bored and use this energy to play the guitar and cook, it will make you happy.
However, if you watch TV, it will only make you happy for a while, not for a long time.
So if your child gets bored and you give him an iPad, he won&#39;t be bored anymore, but he won&#39;t learn how to have fun or drive on his own, said Professor Fenske.
And &quot;this separate procedure is being transferred from one situation to another,&quot; the professor said.
Your child will not only learn how to entertain himself, but will gain more self-control in other areas.
I don&#39;t think we really want to celebrate boredom.
But we shouldn&#39;t be too critical of her either.
Rather, our goal should be to feel comfortable when we are out of reach of the constant rumble of activity and technology.
Professor Eastwood agreed.
&quot;We accuse her of being bored even more, but boredom is a painful, restless desire to be associated with something meaningful,&quot; he said.
What people are actually looking for, he said, is a way to relax and enjoy their free time.
&quot;In an environment where we are constantly overstimulated,&quot; he said, &quot;it&#39;s hard to find ways to have fun when the noise goes off.&quot;
