1.2 children
The one who doesn&#39;t take it much lightly is the Singapore government.
It spends $ 1,300 a year on encouraging citizens to have more children.
The government&#39;s marriage and family package provides up to $ 15,000 per child, extends maternity leave, and allocates financial benefits.
