However, there are concerns that these apartments may promote a youthful lifestyle and discourage developers from building large single-family homes.
But Lim Yew Soon, CEO of development developer EL Developers, claims that their &quot;shoe boxes&quot; are selling much faster than larger houses.
&quot;They are more popular, as they sell days to weeks faster than larger houses.
